Music Player ðŸŽµ
A simple web-based music player built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The player allows users to play, pause, and switch between tracks in a playlist, adjust the volume, and view dynamic album covers, track names, and artist names.

Features;
->Play, pause, next, and previous track controls.
->Dynamic display of track name, artist name, and album cover.
->Volume control slider.
->Playlist section for selecting tracks.
->Stylish and responsive design.

Technologies Used;
->HTML
->CSS
->JavaScript
->Font Awesome (for icons)

Usage
Open index.html in your browser:
        ->You can simply double-click the index.html file or right-click and open it with a web browser.

Control the Player:
        ->Use the play, pause, next, and previous buttons to control the playback.
Adjust the volume using the slider.
        ->Click on a song in the playlist to load and play it.

Customize Playlist:
        ->Edit the tracks array in script.js to add or remove songs.
        ->Each song object in tracks should include:
             name: Name of the track.
             path: File path of the audio file.
             cover: File path of the album cover image.
             artist: Artist name.

